          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Energy resolution is one-half the full neutron energy",
                "spread."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR",
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Used either NaI(Tl) detector at 45%",
                "geometry or Ge(Li) detector at 25% geometry. Used",
                "152Eu, 154Eu and 160Tb gamma-ray energies and",
                "branching ratios to determine relative detector",
                "efficiency. Absolute efficiency determined using",
                "calibrated standards of 57Co, 137Cs, 54Mn, 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gold foils sandwiching the targets were",
                "intended as secondary monitors and their thicknesses",
                "were kept sufficiently small to assure that only a",
                "negligible number of neutrons would be removed from",
                "the beam. The primary neutron flux monitor was a 235U",
                "fission chamber. The irradiated samples were counted",
                "either on a 2x1 in. NaI and Ge(Li) gamma-ray detectors",
                "were coupled to a 4096-channel pulse-height analyzer."
              ]
            }
          ],
